The paper discusses a model-based reinforcement learning approach, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The focus is on planning ahead and avoiding costly mistakes, which is relevant to robotics and control systems (cs.RO, cs.SY). The paper also proposes a new type of multi-step model, which could be of interest to researchers in data science (cs.DS).
